author: Sam Goldfarb
title: Tesla Bonds Inch Up After Production Report
text:
Tesla Inc. bonds edged higher Tuesday after the electric-car maker said it had made progress building its first mass-market sedan.
Tesla said it made 9,766 Model 3 sedans in the first quarter, up from 2,425 in the fourth quarter and 260 in the third. It delivered 8,180 Model 3s to customers, below the 12,300 that analysts surveyed by FactSet had anticipated on average.
